<p>Using a compass with sass I do like below for border-radius.</p>  <pre><code>@import "compass";  #test{     background: red;     @include border-radius(5px);     width:50px;     height:50px; } </code></pre>  <p>It's tedious to write @include border-radius(5px); every time. If I use sass's mixin, I will have to do</p>  <pre><code>@mixin radius($radius) {  -webkit-border-radius: $radius; border-radius: $radius; }  .selector {     @include radius(0 0 5px 5px); } </code></pre>  <p>Which is not using compass anymore. Hmm is there a way to handle better in case?</p>